    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-14T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="836"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d836">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Korea/7–1448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-14T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 14, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3186. Reference <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 3147 dated July 13, 5
                    p. m. 1. Dening today handed officer of Embassy lengthy memorandum giving
                    British objections to recognition of new government in South Korea as “National
                    Government of Korea envisaged by <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> resolutions”.
                    As these are familiar to Department, shall not telegraph full text unless so
                    instructed but shall send airmail.<note n="1" xml:id="d836fn1">Despatch 1570,
                        July 16, from London, not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>2. Following is text proposed substitute statement referred to in Paragraph Two
                    of <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 3147: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Government of the United States considers the administration which
                            has established itself in South Korea as a result of the elections held
                            there on May 10 to be the government envisaged in the terms of the
                            resolutions of the General Assembly and of the Interim Committee of the
                            United Nations”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Department pass Seoul.<note n="2" xml:id="d836fn2">This was done July 15, 3 a.
                        m.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
